main event: An observation of two celestial objects mistaken for planets at Luke AFB, Arizona, on 25 October 1965.
interesting points: The objects exhibited changes in direction and brightness during the observation,The observer initially thought the objects were planets but later considered them as celestial objects,The objects were visible for a total of 2 hours,The weather was hazy, but visibility was good,The observer had no prior knowledge of astronomy or meteorology.
sighted object: two celestial objects, possibly Venus and Jupiter
witness description: observer with no knowledge of astronomy.
